			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>International Tender Coordinator Job Description</strong></p>
<p>
TRANSLATED SRL is a leading Multi-Language Service Provider, based in Rome, Italy, and founded in 2000 by a linguist and a computer scientist with the goal of exploiting technology to increase the quality of human translation, while reducing its turnaround time and cost. We have always stood apart from our competitors due to our capacity to integrate technology into the translation process. Today, our team is made up of linguists, computer scientists, project managers, language fanatics and over 68,000 freelance translators managing translation work for over 26,000 customers.</p>
<p>
TRANSLATED is recruiting an <strong>International Tender Coordinator</strong> to join our growing team in a 6 month internship. The Tender Coordinator will perform a vital role within the business, working closely with and reporting to TRANSLATED&rsquo;s Director of Business Development. The Tender Coordinator will be responsible for preparing and submitting tender applications. The Tender Coordinator will assist in the recruiting, drafting and submission of quality, credible and impactful documentation for tender proposals to secure new business for the organization.</p>
<p>
This is a key role that requires an ability to work under pressure to demanding deadlines, escalating issues as required and creating clear and compelling documentation as part of competitive proposals and tenders in response to solicited and unsolicited opportunities. Our services are delivered across a diverse client portfolio which requires the applicant to have a flexible and analytical approach.</p>
<p>
<strong>Key Responsibilities</strong><br />
&bull; Work in accordance with TRANSLATED&rsquo;s strategic plan and core values.<br />
&bull; Produce and submit initial expressions of interest where required<br />
&bull; Draft formal tender documentation for review, approval and submission<br />
&bull; Identify, recruit and validate the appropriate vendor resources specific to each tender as well as collect, review and edit the required documentation<br />
&bull; Manage inputs from TRANSLATED&rsquo;s project management, account management and development teams where appropriate to ensure all relevant information is obtained for submissions in accordance with deadlines<br />
&bull; Ensure all proposals and tenders are compliant, grammatically correct, conform to TRANSLATED&rsquo;s business objectives and are without errors<br />
&bull; Ensure the final documentation packages are well produced, professionally presented and delivered to the appropriate address in advance of deadlines<br />
&bull; Support staff and manage the tender proposal submission process<br />
&bull; Participate in regular meetings to discuss current and forthcoming opportunities</p>
<p>
<strong>Specifications</strong><br />
&bull; A university degree in one of the following areas: Business, Communications, Languages and/or Translation<br />
&bull; At least 1 year verifiable, successful and relevant work experience in one of the following areas: Tender Proposals, Grant Writing, Project Management, Business Development, Vendor Management and/or Communications Coordination<br />
&bull; Professional, credible, and comfortable in dealing directly with clients and vendors with excellent people and relationship management skills<br />
&bull; Excellent communicator, both verbal and written skills, with the ability to see things from the other people&rsquo;s point of view<br />
&bull; Able to work under tight deadlines, remain calm under pressure, and effectively plan and manage own time and workload<br />
&bull; Able to work with a team, scheduling and setting clear deadlines to ensure timely submission of tenders and proposals<br />
&bull; Fluency in English and at least 1 additional language<br />
&bull; Excellent computer, MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint and typing skills as well as proficient with using the Internet as a research tool. Database skills are also a plus, but not required<br />
&bull; Above all, passionate about TECHNOLOGY, people, business and languages, self-driven, results-oriented with a positive outlook, a clear focus on delivering high quality work, and a desire for new experiences and responsibilities</p>
<p>
<strong>How to apply:</strong><br />
To express your interest in this position please submit a cover letter, outlining why you are the perfect candidate for this position, a current CV and 3 professional references.</p>
]]></description>
