			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>General Description</strong></p>
<p>
Join a web company working on new technologies that will disrupt the language industry and create innovative services within the translation market. You will work with an international team that is using artificial intelligence technology and web information retrieval to help professional translators being more productive and to provide more efficient services to translation customers through automation and disintermediation.</p>
<p>
You will help us to develop Matecat (<a href="http://www.matecat.com">http://www.matecat.com</a>), a new web-based product aimed at creating a new translation environment that integrates innovative approaches to machine translation and increases productivity in translation.</p>
<p>
<strong>Primary Objectives</strong></p>
<p>
You will be involved in developing the server side core of MateCat and in improving the communication with the user interface and external services used by the tool.</p>
<p>
You will be involved in all stages of our engineering life cycle, including architectural design,&nbsp; and will be responsible to write high quality code, in terms of performance, readability and maintainability.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>During the first 30 days, </strong>you will work closely with the UX Engineer and will be involved in developing planned features like advanced filters and integration of an external service using NLP to extract terminology from big data.</li>
<li>
<strong>After this initial period</strong>, you will gradually take on new responsibilities to work autonomously on the design and development of further components.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Skills and Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
World-class programming skills.</li>
<li>
At least 5 years of professional experience as a web developer</li>
<li>
In-depth knowledge of: PHP &gt;=5.2 / MySQL</li>
<li>
In-depth knowledge of: regular expressions / REST webservices</li>
<li>
Knowledge of client side technologies : JQuery / HTML5 (included Websockets) / CSS3</li>
<li>
Big data and scalability focused technologies like:&nbsp; NodeJS, MongoDB</li>
<li>
Degree, master or doctorate in IT or computer engineering.</li>
<li>
A strong knowledge of both written and spoken English.</li>
<li>
Good relationship and communication skills.</li>
<li>
Propensity to work in an international environment.</li>
</ul>
<p>
We are looking for an open minded person that loves programming, and is focused on the quality and performances.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Company Description</strong></p>
<p>
Translated is a language service provider that is changing the language industry by using NLP and AI technology to make translators&rsquo; life easier by minimizing repetitive tasks and making customers happier by reducing traditional agency intermediation.</p>
<p>
Translated was founded in 1999 and currently manages over 70,000 translators in 110 countries to provide translation services to more than 30,000 customers.</p>
<p>
Translated is focused on serving large businesses, startup and web 2.0 companies that need to speed-up and automate their globalization processes.</p>
<p>
Corporations like <strong>Google</strong>, <strong>Amazon</strong> and <strong>HP</strong> use our technologies and services in their localization processes.</p>
<p>
Translated uses NLP and AI technology to make translators&rsquo; life easier by minimizing repetitive tasks and making customers happier by reducing traditional agency intermediation.</p>
<p>
Thanks to its innovative approach to language technology, Translated has been chosen by Google to create new services for flagship products such as <strong>YouTube</strong> (&nbsp;<a href="http://techcrunch.com/2013/02/20/youtube-partners-with-gengo-and-translated-net-to-make-ordering-paid-caption-translations-easier/">http://techcrunch.com/2013/02/20/youtube-partners-with-gengo-and-translated-net-to-make-ordering-paid-caption-translations-easier/</a>) and, recently, &nbsp;the translation of the apps in the<strong>&nbsp;Google Play Store</strong> ( <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9pmPa_KxsAM#t=40m44s">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9pmPa_KxsAM#t=40m44s</a>)</p>
<p>
Translated has created MyMemory (<a href="http://mymemory.translated.net">http://mymemory.translated.net</a>), the world&rsquo;s largest translation memory, that combines machine translation with over 600 million human contributions. Translated uses MyMemory to increase the quality and speed of translation by suggesting sentences that have already been translated.</p>
<p>
<strong>MateCat</strong> is the next big thing on which Translated is currently working: a web-based software that pushes forward what is considered the new frontier of Computer Assisted Translation technology, that is, how to effectively and ergonomically integrate Machine Translation within the human translation workflow.</p>
