<strong>General description</strong><br />
<br />
Reporting to the Account Manager, you will be a key point of contact for Translated&#39;s clients, as they continue to use our services.</p>
<p>
<strong>Primary objectives</strong><br />
<br />
You will be responsible for receiving individual client requests for some of Translated&#39;s enterprise and institutional clients, mostly German. You will have full responsibility for scoping requests and turning them into client projects, ensuring that appropriate resources are allocated, and guaranteeing a successful handover to project managers, ensuring passage of all relevant information to ensure project success.</p>
<p>
You will have a major contribution in ensuring profitability and success of projects, driving customer retention.</p>
<p>
You will proactively foresee any projects that will require non-standard management, briefing Account Managers and Project Managers. You will work with them in order to ensure effective resolution.</p>
<p>
You will be a key communicator for Translated, also helping new customers by providing them information about our service, and also by drawing up price proposals for them.&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>During first 60 days</strong> You will be involved, as project manager, in our core operations in order to understand how the localization industry, and Translated in particular, work.</li>
<li>
<strong>During the first 90 days </strong>You will start receiving translation requests from Translated&#39;s key clients and start scoping and preparing projects for handover.</li>
<li>
<strong>By the end of the 90 days</strong> You will be a key point of contact in Translated for the clients you are assigned.</li>
<li>
<strong>After 12 months&nbsp;</strong>You will be contributing directly to the revenue and profit generated by the clients you service.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Skill and Experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
You will be mother tongue German or perfect German, perfect English&nbsp;and Italian,</li>
<li>
You will have already worked in customer facing roles,</li>
<li>
You will have an ambitious and optimistic nature, and will look to constantly improve your profile with new experience, knowledge, and expertise,</li>
<li>
Ideally, you will have already worked in a web company, and have a good understanding of web technologies,</li>
<li>
Ideally, you may have already worked in the localization sector,</li>
<li>
You will have achieved your degree to an excellent standard, and will be able to demonstrate sound business/commercial sense.</li>
</ul>
<p>
If you think we are looking for you, send us your CV, and tell us how you can make a difference.</p>
<p>
<strong>Company Description</strong></p>
<p>
Translated is a language service provider focused on serving large businesses, startup and web 2.0 companies that need to speed-up and automate their globalization processes. Thanks to its innovative approach to language technology, it has been chosen by Google to create new services for flagship products such as YouTube (http://techcrunch.com/2013/02/20/youtube-partners-with-gengo-and-translated-net-to-make-ordering-paid-caption-translations-easier/) and, recently, for the translation of apps published in the Google Play Store ( http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9pmPa_KxsAM#t=40m44s). Moreover, corporations like Amazon, Expedia and HP use our technologies and services in their localization processes. Choose a career at Translated and enjoy an innovative international environment where challenging and interesting work is part of daily life.</p>
<p>
<strong>Translated </strong>was founded in <strong>1999 </strong>and currently manages over <strong>73,000</strong> translators in 110 countries to provide translation services to more than 30,000 customers.<br />
